This paper deals with the quantization of transmit beamforming vectors and signature vectors in wireless communication systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to reduce the search complexity of the random vector quantization (RVQ) codebook, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper includes examples of the performance of the proposed method, which could be considered as a machine learning (cs.MM) or learning (cs.LG) problem.
